  "text": "The Kubernetes admission webhook processing chain is implemented across several key components:\n\n## Generic Webhook Dispatcher Foundation\nThe generic webhook dispatcher is implemented in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/generic/webhook.go` and `generic/interfaces.go`. The `Webhook` struct (line 50 in webhook.go) serves as the abstract base class for all webhook admission plugins, containing infrastructure like `ClientManager`, namespace/object matchers, and a `Dispatcher` interface. The `Dispatch` method (line 255 in webhook.go) is the core entry point that retrieves webhooks from the source and delegates to the specific dispatcher implementation. The `ShouldCallHook` method (line 158) evaluates whether a webhook should be invoked based on namespace selectors, object selectors, and match conditions.\n\n## Mutating Webhook Dispatcher with Reinvocation Logic\nThe mutating webhook dispatcher is implemented in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/mutating/dispatcher.go`. The `mutatingDispatcher` type (line 68) implements the `Dispatcher` interface and is created by the `Plugin` type in `mutating/plugin.go`. The key innovation is reinvocation support: the `Dispatch` method (line 105) uses a `webhookReinvokeContext` stored in the admission attributes' reinvocation context. The reinvocation logic is implemented in `mutating/reinvocationcontext.go`: when the `callAttrMutatingHook` method (line 244) modifies an object, it triggers `RequireReinvokingPreviouslyInvokedPlugins` to mark eligible webhooks (those with `IfNeededReinvocationPolicy`) for reinvocation. The reinvocation context tracks which webhooks should be reinvoked via `ShouldReinvokeWebhook` (line 35 in reinvocationcontext.go). This ensures that if earlier mutations trigger subsequent webhooks, all affected webhooks are reinvoked in a controlled manner.\n\n## Validating Webhook Dispatcher with Parallel Dispatch\nThe validating webhook dispatcher is implemented in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/validating/dispatcher.go`. The `validatingDispatcher` type (line 55) implements the `Dispatcher` interface. The key difference from mutating webhooks is parallel execution: the `Dispatch` method (line 88) uses goroutines with `sync.WaitGroup` (line 126) to spawn concurrent validation calls. It first collects all matching webhooks in a loop (lines 96-111), then launches goroutines for each webhook (lines 129-228). Each goroutine runs `callHook` in parallel, and errors are collected via an error channel. This allows validating webhooks to execute concurrently since they don't modify the object, improving performance.\n\n## WebhookAccessor Abstraction Layer\nThe `WebhookAccessor` interface (line 37 in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/accessors.go`) provides a unified abstraction for both mutating and validating webhooks. It defines methods like `GetMutatingWebhook`, `GetValidatingWebhook`, `GetRESTClient`, `GetCompiledMatcher`, and properties like `GetRules`, `GetFailurePolicy`, `GetNamespaceSelector`, `GetObjectSelector`, and `GetMatchConditions`. The `mutatingWebhookAccessor` type (line 95) implements this interface for `v1.MutatingWebhook` objects. The accessor pattern uses sync.Once to lazily initialize expensive operations like REST client creation and match condition compilation, improving efficiency.\n\n## API Type Definitions\nThe webhook configuration types are defined in `kubernetes/api` repository's `admissionregistration/v1/types.go`. The `MutatingWebhookConfiguration` type (line 755) and `ValidatingWebhookConfiguration` type (line 721) represent cluster-scoped configuration resources. `MutatingWebhookConfiguration` contains a list of `MutatingWebhook` objects (line 766) that can modify requests, while `ValidatingWebhookConfiguration` contains `ValidatingWebhook` objects that only validate. Both are loaded dynamically by configuration managers that implement the `Source` interface (generic/interfaces.go, line 32).\n\n## Processing Chain Summary\n1. When a request arrives, the mutating or validating plugin's `Admit`/`Validate` method is invoked\n2. This delegates to the generic `Webhook.Dispatch` method\n3. The generic dispatcher retrieves webhooks and calls `ShouldCallHook` to filter applicable webhooks\n4. For mutating webhooks: the sequential dispatcher invokes each webhook via `callAttrMutatingHook`, applies patches to the object, and manages reinvocation context\n5. For validating webhooks: the dispatcher spawns goroutines for parallel execution via `callHook`\n6. Both dispatchers use the `WebhookAccessor` abstraction to interact with webhook configurations\n7. All webhook configurations are defined via `MutatingWebhookConfiguration` and `ValidatingWebhookConfiguration` API types"
